[thinking] **Clarifying constructor access**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether a nested public static class needs a public no-argument constructor. For a public class, the default constructor shares the same access level, which means it’d be public. I believe this holds true for a static nested class too; it should have a public default constructor. It seems fine to assume the constructor access aligns with the class access level. So if the class is public, the default constructor should be public as well.
[thinking] 
